ref> Yamato,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://myfigurecollection.net/item/1770_vampire_savior_morrigan_aensland_yamato |title=Vampire Savior \u2013 Morrigan Aensland (Yamato) |publisher=Myfigurecollection.net |accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://myfigurecollection.net/item/3772_vampire_savior_morrigan_aensland_1_7_heavy_gauge_v |title=Vampire Savior \u2013 Morrigan Aensland \u2013 1/7 \u2013 Heavy Gauge Ver. (Yamato) |publisher=Myfigurecollection.net |date=2013-03-24 |accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://myfigurecollection.net/item/23947_vampire_savior_morrigan_aensland_1_6_capcom_girls_ |title=Vampire Savior \u2013 Morrigan Aensland \u2013 1/6 \u2013 Capcom Girls Collection (Yamato) |publisher=Myfigurecollection.net |accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref> Yoiko,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://myfigurecollection.net/item/23396_vampire_savior_morrigan_aensland_1_6_utatane_ver_y |title=Vampire Savior \u2013 Morrigan Aensland \u2013 1/6 \u2013 Utatane ver. (Yoiko Q) |publisher=Myfigurecollection.net |accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref> and Yujin,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://myfigurecollection.net/item/11237_vampire_savior_morrigan_aensland_sr_capcom_vs_snk_ |title=Vampire Savior \u2013 Morrigan Aensland \u2013 SR Capcom vs SNK Part 2 (Yujin) |publisher=Myfigurecollection.net |accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://myfigurecollection.net/item/11214_vampire_savior_morrigan_aensland_sr_vampire_savior |title=Vampire Savior \u2013 Morrigan Aensland \u2013 SR Vampire Savior Part 3 (Yujin) |publisher=Myfigurecollection.net |accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://myfigurecollection.net/item/23948_vampire_savior_morrigan_aensland_1_6_sr_dx_yujin |title=Vampire Savior \u2013 Morrigan Aensland \u2013 1/6 \u2013 SR DX (Yujin) |publisher=Myfigurecollection.net |accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref> among many others.\n\nOther Morrigan-themed merchandise include Capcom's wall scrolls and posters,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-capcom.com/ec/srDispProductListProductLink/doProductTreeLink/1/1/A10005007/10/10/srDispProductList/ |title=\u30a4\u30fc\u30ab\u30d7\u30b3\u30f3 \u2502 \u30ab\u30d7\u30b3\u30f3\u30aa\u30d5\u30a3\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u30b7\u30e7\u30c3\u30d7 |publisher=E-capcom.com |date= |accessdate=2015-08-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-capcom.com/ec/srDispProductListProductLink/doProductTreeLink/1/1/A10005007/11/10/srDispProductList/|title=Big Vampire Tapestry / Morrigan & Lilith|publisher=E-Capcom|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://shop.capcom.com/store/capcomus/en_US/pd/ThemeID.1944700/productID.285166400/Darkstalkers-Movie-Poster-Set.html|title=Capcom Store \u2013 Buy Darkstalkers Poster Sets|accessdate=8 September 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140904155033/http://shop.capcom.com/store/capcomus/en_US/pd/ThemeID.1944700/productID.285166400/Darkstalkers-Movie-Poster-Set.html|archivedate=4 September 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.inside-games.jp/article/2018/02/14/112765.html|script-title=ja:\u300c\u30e2\u30ea\u30ac\u30f3\u300d\u306e\u30d3\u30c3\u30b0\u30d0\u30b9\u30bf\u30aa\u30eb\u304c\u30a4\u30fc\u30ab\u30d7\u30b3\u30f3\u3067\u53d7\u6ce8\u958b\u59cb\u3001\u30d9\u30f3\u30ac\u30b9\u63cf\u304d\u4e0b\u308d\u3057\u30a4\u30e9\u30b9\u30c8\u3092\u4f7f\u7528|last=|first=|date=|work=\u30a4\u30f3\u30b5\u30a4\u30c9|access-date=2018-07-30|language=ja}}</ref> T-shirts,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-capcom.com/ec/srDispProductListProductLink/doProductTreeLink/1/1/A10005008/10/10/srDispProductList/|title=Vampire T-shirt / Morrigan / S|publisher=|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://shop.capcom.com/store/capcomus/en_US/pd/ThemeID.1944700/productID.265721600/Darkstalkers-Tshirt-3pack.html|title=Capcom Store \u2013 Buy Darkstalkers t-shirt 3-pack|accessdate=8 September 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140904152631/http://shop.capcom.com/store/capcomus/en_US/pd/ThemeID.1944700/productID.265721600/Darkstalkers-Tshirt-3pack.html|archivedate=4 September 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://game.watch.impress.co.jp/docs/news/1080373.html|title=\u300c\u30e2\u30f3\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30cf\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc \u3086\u308bT\u30b7\u30e3\u30c4\u300d\u3001\u7b2c2\u5f3e\u306e\u53d7\u6ce8\u3092\u958b\u59cb \u300c\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30c0\u30fc\u98db\u7adc\u300d\u3001\u300c\u30ad\u30e3\u30d7\u30c6\u30f3\u30b3\u30de\u30f3\u30c9\u30fc\u300d\u306e\u30aa\u30ea\u30b8\u30ca\u30eb\u30c7\u30b6\u30a4\u30f3T\u30b7\u30e3\u30c4\u3082\u767b\u5834|last=|first=|date=2017-09-12|work=GAME Watch|access-date=2018-07-30|language=ja-JP}}</ref> covers,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-capcom.com/ec/srDispProductListProductLink/doProductTreeLink/1/1/A10005010/17/10/srDispProductList/|title=E-Capcom Limited Original smartphone cover Vampire Morrigan & Felicia (Phase 2)|publisher=|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref> a large microfiber towel,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.inside-games.jp/article/2018/02/14/112765.html|script-title=ja:\u300c\u30e2\u30ea\u30ac\u30f3\u300d\u306e\u30d3\u30c3\u30b0\u30d0\u30b9\u30bf\u30aa\u30eb\u304c\u30a4\u30fc\u30ab\u30d7\u30b3\u30f3\u3067\u53d7\u6ce8\u958b\u59cb\u3001\u30d9\u30f3\u30ac\u30b9\u63cf\u304d\u4e0b\u308d\u3057\u30a4\u30e9\u30b9\u30c8\u3092\u4f7f\u7528|last=|first=|date=|work=\u30a4\u30f3\u30b5\u30a4\u30c9|access-date=2018-11-23|language=ja}}</ref> and so forth. She is very prominently<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2014/05/18/udon-entertainment-brings-us-an-enormous-darkstalkers-art-book/85505/ |title=Udon Entertainment Brings Us An Enormous Darkstalkers Art Book |publisher=Hardcore Gamer |date=2014-05-18 |accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref> featured in various ''Darkstalkers'' art books, including adorning the covers of UDON-published books ''Darkstalkers Graphic File'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Darkstalkers-Graphic-File-Capcom/dp/1897376049|title=Darkstalkers Graphic File: Capcom: 9781897376041: Amazon.com: Books|accessdate=8 September 2014}}</ref> ''Darkstalkers Tribute'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Darkstalkers-Tribute-Jim-Zubkavich/dp/1897376103|title=Darkstalkers Tribute: Udon, Jim Zubkavich: 9781897376102: Amazon.com: Books|author=|publisher=|accessdate=8 September 2014}}</ref> and ''Darkstalkers Official Complete Works'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.udonentertainment.com/blog/tag/darkstalkers-official-complete-works/|title=UDON Entertainment \u00bb Darkstalkers: Official Complete Works|accessdate=8 September 2014}}</ref> as well as in the collectible card game ''[[Universal Fighting System]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/PlayUFS/photos/pb.179894002082946.-2207520000.1416072407./662225263849815/|title=UFS: The Universal Fighting System's Photos \u2013 UFS: The Universal Fighting System|publisher=Facesbook.com|accessdate=2015-07-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/PlayUFS/photos/pb.179894002082946.-2207520000.1416072421./630536980351977/|title=UFS: The Universal Fighting System's Photos \u2013 UFS: The Universal Fighting System|publisher=Facesbook.com|accessdate=2015-07-16}}</ref> for which the starter set Morrigan Collector's Tin<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jascogames.com/product/darkstalkers-ufs-morrigan-tin/|title=Jasco Games|publisher=Jasco Games|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129035649/http://jascogames.com/product/darkstalkers-ufs-morrigan-tin/|archivedate=29 November 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> was released in 2014.\n\n==Cultural impact==\nAccording to Kotaku's Mike Fahey in 2012, \"Morrigan Aensland from Capcom's ''Darkstalkers'' is one of the most widely depicted characters in video games. Her distinctive features have spawned dozens of statues, hundreds of [[cosplay]]s and thousands of pieces of [[fan art]].\"<ref name=sultry/> In anime series ''[[Ultimate Girls]]'', the character Tsubomi makes an appearance dressed up as Morrigan.<ref>In the second episode, at 8:22 minutes.</ref> Morrigan has featured in many [[doujinshi]] unofficial self-published content,<ref>''GameAxis Unwired'', November 2008, page 17.</ref> including [[erotic comics]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/HobbyConsolas089/Hobby_Consolas_089#page/n119/mode/1up/|title=Hobby Consolas 089|publisher=Archive.org|accessdate=2014-05-04}}</ref> such as [[Hiroaki Samura]]'s ''Night of the Succubus'' (\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30d0\u30b9\u306e\u591c) and pornographic films like ''Layers Cute Hard: Yuuna''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/5902602/japanese-porn-is-overdosing-on-video-games-and-anime/|title=Japanese Porn Is Overdosing on Video Games and Anime|publisher=Kotaku.com|accessdate=2014-06-16}}</ref> One of the color palettes of the fighting game ''[[Skullgirls]]'' character Ms. Fortune is a homage to Morrigan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/videos/2011/11/07/skullgirls-friday-fights|title=Negaduck vs Dyselon Square Off in Skullgirls \u2013 IGN Video|date=2011-11-07|publisher=Ign.com|accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Morrigan JackalsMotives.jpg|thumb|left|[[Cosplay]]er Kassandra Leigh Purcell as Morrigan at [[Katsucon]] 2014]]\n\nAccording to Kotaku's Brian Ashcraft in 2012, \"Since debuting in 1994's ''Darkstalkers: The Night Warriors'', Morrigan Aensland has become one of gaming's most iconic characters. A fan service favorite, Morrigan continues to attract cosplayers, eager to put on succubus's revealing outfit.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/5925021/go-on-let-morrigan-drive-you-batty/|title=Go On, Let Morrigan Drive You Batty|publisher=Kotaku.com|accessdate=2014-06-16}}</ref> Already in 1996, Capcom's representatives were quoted as saying: \"If we add female characters, it is very popular. Have you ever been to the {{sic|'Cost-play'}} show in Japan? People dress up as Morrigan or Felicia to [costume-]play the games.\"<ref name=mms/> [[Helen McCarthy]]'s 2009 book ''500 Essential Anime Movies: The Ultimate Guide'' cited Morrigan as an example of the popularity of the ''Darkstalkers'' character designs, with fans frequently cosplaying as the character at various conventions since the original game's release.<ref>{{cite book|title=500 Essential Anime Movies: The Ultimate Guide|author=McCarthy, Helen|publisher=Collins Design|year=2009|isbn=0-06-147450-9|page=214}}</ref> In 2010, [[UGO.com|UGO]]'s Chris Plante called her \"''Darkstalkers''{{'}} most recognizable character [and] also wildly popular with cosplayers\"<ref name=sp/> and French television network [[TF1]] included Morrigan among the sexiest video game characters to cosplay and one of the most charismatic.<ref>[http://lci.tf1.fr/cinema/news/le-top-15-des-cosplay-les-plus-sexy-du-jeu-video-partie-2-5769009.html Le Top 15 des Cosplay les plus Sexy du jeu vid\u00e9o (partie 2)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160108202845/http://lci.tf1.fr/cinema/news/le-top-15-des-cosplay-les-plus-sexy-du-jeu-video-partie-2-5769009.html|date=8 January 2016}}, TF1, 12 March 2010.</ref> In [[GameFront]]'s 2011 article showcasing some of Morrigan (and Lilith) cosplayers, Phil Owen called it \"probably the sexiest gallery I\u2019ve ever posted.\"<ref>Phil Owen, [http://www.gamefront.com/50-morrigan-aensland-cosplayers-way-sexy-pics/ 50 Morrigan Aensland Cosplayers (WAY SEXY PICS)], GameFront, 14 February 2011.</ref> [[Destructoid]]'s Brittany Vincent wrote in 2014: \"For some, Morrigan Aensland is the face of ''Darkstalkers''. For every cosplayer who runs around in loose-fitting fur as Felicia, there are a hundred Morrigans basking in the glory that only comes from hitting up cons in a winged gymnastics costume.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.destructoid.com/capcom-is-releasing-a-new-morrigan-figure-274553.phtml|title=Capcom is releasing a new Morrigan figure|author=Brittany Vincent|publisher=Destructoid|accessdate=2014-05-10}}</ref> \n\nCelebrity cosplayers who portrayed Morrigan include the Filipino [[Alodia Gosiengfiao]] (one of her favorite costumes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/adobomagazine/docs/0311_issuu|title=adobo magazine &#124; May \u2013 June 2011 by Sanserif, Inc|date=|publisher=ISSUU|accessdate=2015-07-16}}</ref>),<ref>[https://issuu.com/unomagazineguam/docs/uno_7th ''UNO GUAM'' May\u2013June 2011], pages 74\u201375.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kotaku.com.au/2010/11/darkstalkers-cosplay-has-never-been-sexier/|title=Darkstalkers Cosplay Has Never Been Sexier &#124; Kotaku Australia|date=2010-11-10|publisher=Kotaku.com.au|accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref> and the Americans [[Jessica Nigri]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.548740055170648.1073741826.432067370171251|title=Jessica Nigri as Morrigan from Darkstalkers in Yakuta|publisher=Facesbook.com|accessdate=2015-07-16}}</ref> and [[Linda Le|Linda \"Vampy\" Le]], who called Morrigan \"just damn amazing\" as \"favorite by far\" character and \"the epitome of Succubus chic,\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nerdsociety.com/cosplay-interview-linda-le-aka-vampy/|title=Cosplay Interview: Linda Le aka Vampy &#124;|date=2010-12-14|publisher=Nerdsociety.com|accessdate=2014-06-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ampedasia.com/article/Linda-Le-aka-Vampy-Interview/|title=Linda Le aka Vampy|date=2010-10-07|publisher=Amped Asia|accessdate=2014-06-24}}</ref> but noted it was difficult to make.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://themovieandme.blogspot.com/2013/09/stgcc-2013-vampy-bit-me-linda-le.html|title=The Movie and Me \u2013 Movie Reviews and more: STGCC 2013: Vampy Bit Me (Linda Le) interview|last=Jong|first=Jedd|date=2013-09-05|publisher=Themovieandme.blogspot.com|accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref>  Another cosplayer, [[Meg Turney]], said she would \"love to do Morrigan someday\" even as \"whoever designed the costume without shoulder straps was either someone who hated cosplayers and wanted them to suffer \u2013 or a dude.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.g4tv.com/thefeed/blog/post/722281/cosplay-nation-experts-take-on-the-world-of-video-game-fashion/|title=Cosplay Nation \u2013 Experts Take On The World of Video Game Fashion|date=2012-03-30|publisher=G4tv.com|accessdate=2014-06-29}}</ref> One famous portrayal of Morrigan was done by Lindze Merritt,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://socialnewsdaily.com/16220/top-cosplay-girls-to-follow-on-twitter/|title=Top Cosplay Girls To Follow On Twitter [Photos&#93;|date=2013-08-20|publisher=Socialnewsdaily.com|accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref> who later was hired to portray Morrigan during the official ''Marvel Vs. Capcom 3'' Fight Club event in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://alphacounter.com/2010/11/27/lindze-merrit-cosplay-interview/|title=Lindze Merritt Cosplay Interview \u2013 The Grey Ghost|author=Sean Ryan|date=2010-11-27|publisher=Alpha Counter|accessdate=2016-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140628175958/http://alphacounter.com/2010/11/27/lindze-merrit-cosplay-interview/|archive-date=28 June 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shock.co/cultura/articulos/guia-shock-para-disfrutar-del-salon-del-ocio-y-la-fantasia-42480|title=Gu\u00eda Shock para disfrutar del Sal\u00f3n del Ocio y la Fantas\u00eda|publisher=Shock \u2013 M\u00fasica, cine, entretenimiento y cultura joven en Colombia|language=Es}}</ref> Morrigan was the first cosplay of Spanish cosplayer known as \"Judy Helsing\", who later portrayed [[Bayonetta (character)|Bayonetta]] for [[Nintendo]] in ''[[Playboy]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.meristation.com/nintendo-wii-u/noticias/judy-helsing-la-espectacular-bayonetta-espanola/1365/2017229|title=Judy Helsing, la espectacular Bayonetta espa\u00f1ola|author=Enrique Garc\u00eda @enriquegper|date=25 October 2014|work=Meristation|language=Es}}</ref> {{Clear}}\n\n==Reception==\n===Popularity===\nMorrigan is widely seen as the most iconic character of ''Darkstalkers'', arguably even more than the franchise itself,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.eventhubs.com/news/2015/oct/17/how-did-morrigan-become-arguably-more-popular-franchise-shes-nostalgic-gamers-enticing-recount-her-history-eye-opener/|title=How did Morrigan become arguably more popular than the franchise she's from? Nostalgic Gamer's enticing recount of her history is an eye opener|work=EventHubs|access-date=2018-07-13|language=en}}</ref> and one of the most popular female characters of video games in general. In 1996, ''[[Mean Machines Sega]]'' described her as \"one of the most bewitching girl characters ever to appear in gaming, which explains her huge fan base in Japan \u2013 comprising men and women!\"<ref name=mms>''Mean Machines Sega'' 40 (February 1996), pages 18\u201320.</ref> Morrigan was named the 17th-best character of 1997 by Japanese arcade gaming magazine ''Gamest'',<ref>{{cite journal |title=\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u30af\u30bf\u30fc\u8cde |trans-title=Best Character Award |journal=Gamest |issue=212 |date=30 January 1998|page=102 |author=}}</ref> while the Japanese ''Sega Saturn Magazine'' ranked her as the seventh-best female character on the [[Sega Saturn]].<ref>''SSM'' 25/1997, page 125.</ref> Later, Japanese magazine ''[[Famitsu]]'' ranked Morrigan as the 12th-best video game heroine of the 1990s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.famitsu.com/magazine/otona/heroine/2015/1990_list.html |title=1990\u5e74\u4ee3\u30d2\u30ed\u30a4\u30f3\u30ea\u30b9\u30c8\uff5c\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u30df\u30af\u30b9 |publisher=Famitsu.com |date= |accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref> Morrigan was chosen as one of the 20 \"[[muse]]s\" of video games by Brazilian magazine ''SuperGamePower'' in 2001.<ref>{{cite journal |date=April 2001 |title=As Musas Do Videogame |trans-title=The Muses of Videogames |url=https://archive.org/stream/SuperGamePower_Ano_07_No._085_2001-04_Nova_Cultural_BR_pt#page/n11/mode/2up |journal=SuperGamePower |issue=85 |page=13 |language=Portuguese }}</ref> Featuring her and Felicia in their ''Girls of Gaming'' special in 2003, ''[[Play (US magazine)|play]]'' introduced the two are famous for how they \"unified the haunting with the erotic, along with previously unseen level of animation and creature design.\"<ref>''Play magazine presents: Girls of Gaming'' #1.</ref> Kotaku's Luke Plunkett wrote he has \"always found Morrigan a fascinating character. ''Darkstalkers'' is a fairly obscure series, one which few people will have played on a regular basis, and yet Morrigan is always front and centre when it comes to fan art and cosplay.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/5849767/hello-morrigan-youre-looking-lovely-today |title=Hello Morrigan, You're Looking Lovely Today |publisher=Kotaku.com |accessdate=2014-06-16}}</ref> ''[[Electronic Gaming Monthly|EGM]]'' even reported on a newborn girl given Morrigan's name as a tribute.<ref>''EGM'' 175 (Fall 2004), page 22.</ref> Tom Goulter of GamesRadar wrote in 2013: \"Few characters have consumed as much [[fan fiction|fan-ink]] as ''Darkstalkers''{{'}} seductive succubus and the ''Street Fighter'' series' [[Chun-Li|high-kicking bunhead]]. Both have sustained popularity for decades (Morrigan's 20th anniversary comes next year), and they outlasted countless imitators to become standouts of the Capcom cast.\"<ref>Tom Goulter, [https://www.gamesradar.com/project-x-zone-roster/ Project X Zone roster: Meet all 60 playable characters], GamesRadar, 24 January 2013.</ref> GamesRadar staff included Morrigan among the 30 best characters in the three decades of Capcom's history (since 1983), commenting \"it\u2019s hard to think of any more famous for their beauty\" and noting \"she has a deeper backstory than some fan art would lead you to believe.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/30-best-capcom-characters/ |title=The 30 best Capcom characters of the last 30 years |publisher=GamesRadar |date=2013-06-25 |accessdate=2014-04-12}}</ref> \n\n{{quote box|quote=This sultry succubus is one of fighting games' leading ladies, striking a balance between the dignified seriousness of [[Chun-Li]] and the hyper-sexualized cleavage-heaving antics of [[Mai Shiranui]]. ... Besides her full-time gig as a [[Sexual fantasy|male fantasy]], Morrigan\u2019s made quite a name for herself, showing up in almost every Capcom crossover and spin-off.<ref name=best/>|source=Lucas Sullivan, [[GamesRadar]] (2012)|width=30%|}}\n\nAccording to [[GameSpot]], \"Morrigan has been a mainstay in the Capcom crossover fighting games and is definitely a fan favorite.\"<ref name=gs/> ''Play'' featured her in the \"Girls of Anime\" special,<ref>{{cite journal |last=Halverson |first=Dave |author2=Mike Griffin |author3=Heather Anne Campbell |author4=Matt Cabral |author5=Eric L. Patterson  |title=Girls of Anime |journal=[[Play (US magazine)|play]] |volume=1 |issue= |page=20}}</ref> later regretting her absence in ''Capcom Fighting Evolution'' in their \"Girls of Gaming\" special.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Halverson |first=Dave |author2=Mike Griffin |author3=Heather Anne Campbell |author4=Matt Cabral |author5=Eric L. Patterson  |title=Girls of Gaming |journal=[[Play (US magazine)|play]] |volume=2 |issue= |page=67}}</ref> [[Crunchyroll]]'s Nate Ming described Morrigan as the \"FACE of the series,\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-feature/2013/03/15-1/feature-fanart-friday-darkstalkers-damnation-edition |title=FEATURE: Fanart Friday \u2013 Darkstalkers' Damnation Edition |publisher=Crunchyroll |date=2013-03-15 |accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref> and ''[[GamesTM]]'' commented that Capcom's choice of Anakaris instead of Morrigan or Talbain to represent ''Darkstalkers'' in the 2005 game ''[[Capcom Fighting Jam]]'' was \"a strange selection, to say the least.\"<ref>''GamesTM'' 29, page 118.</ref> Her costume was one of the two added to ''We Love Golf!'' by popular vote in a poll among players.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/391229/capcom-reveals-new-we-love-golf-costumes/ |title=Capcom Reveals New We Love Golf! Costumes |publisher=Kotaku.com |accessdate=2014-06-16}}</ref> Kotaku's Fahey, calling ''Cross Edge'' an \"RPG fan's wet dream,\" stated that \"a game with [[Etna (Disgaea)|Etna]] and Morrigan together alone is worth eleventy million dollars.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Mike Fahay|url=http://kotaku.com/387992/capcom-nippon-ichi-namco-bandai-gust-and-idea-factory-team-for-rpg-fans-wet-dream |title=Capcom, Nippon Ichi, Namco Bandai, Gust, And Idea Factory Team For RPG Fan's Wet Dream |publisher=Kotaku.com |accessdate=2014-06-16}}</ref> In 2010, ''[[Game Informer]]'' chose Morrigan as one of the twenty Capcom characters they would like to see in a rumored crossover fighting game ''Namco Vs Capcom'', her [[Namco]] side counterpart being [[Ivy Valentine]].<ref>Tim Turi, [https://web.archive.org/web/20131007221927/http://www.gameinformer.com/b/features/archive/2010/07/20/20-namco-vs-capcom-matches-we-d-love-to-see.aspx 20 Namco Vs Capcom Matches We'd Love To See], ''Game Informer'', 20 July 2010.</ref> In 2012, ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'' ranked the \"super sexual but also super deadly\" Morrigan as the 13th \"most dominant\" fighting game character,<ref>Elton Jones, [http://www.complex.com/video-games/2012/05/the-50-most-dominant-fighting-characters-in-video-games/morrigan The 50 Most Dominant Fighting Game Characters], Complex.com, 17 May 2012.</ref> further including  \"Capcom vs. [[DC Universe]]\" as third fighting game crossover idea they would like to see the most, for a battle between Morrigan and [[Wonder Woman]].<ref>[http://www.complex.com/video-games/2012/04/10-fighting-game-crossovers-we-want-to-see/capcom-vs-dc-universe 10 Fighting Game Crossovers We Want To See], Complex.com, 10 April 2012.</ref> That same year, Lucas Sullivan of GamesRadar ranked her as the fourth-best character in the fighting game genre's history<ref name=best>Lucas Sullivan, [https://www.gamesradar.com/top-7-best-fighting-game-characters/ The Top 7\u2026 Best fighting game characters], GamesRadar, 10 September 2012.</ref> and [[WatchMojo.com]] ranked her as the sixth-most iconic fighting game character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.watchmojo.com/video/id/11251/ |title=Top 10 Fighting Game Characters |publisher=WatchMojo.com |date=24 September 2012 |accessdate=2013-10-15}}</ref> Obi Anyanwu of ''Complex'' placed Morrigan ninth in his 2012 list of video game characters that deserve a spin-off<ref>Obi Anyanwu, [http://www.complex.com/video-games/2012/12/25-video-game-characters-that-deserve-a-spinoff/ 25 Video Game Characters That Deserve a Spinoff], Complex.com, 2 January 2012.</ref> and Mike Andronico of Gamenguide named her as number one \"fiercest female in today's fighting games\" who \"has stood the test of time as one of fighting games' most iconic faces\" by 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamenguide.com/articles/6924/20130527/top-10-fiercest-females-todays-fighting-games.htm |title=Top 10: Fiercest Females In Today's Fighting Games : Games |publisher=Gamenguide |date=2013-05-27 |accessdate=2013-06-08}}</ref> In 2016, Crunchyroll's Brittany Vincent described Morrigan as \"a perennial ''Darkstalkers'' favorite, and for good reason. She's gorgeous, powerful, and all-around awesome.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2016/08/13/this-darkstalkers-morrigan-aensland-figure-from-capcom-is-absolutely-gorgeous|title=This \"Darkstalkers\" Morrigan Aensland Figure From Capcom Is Absolutely Gorgeous|work=Crunchyroll|access-date=2018-05-15|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Sex appeal===\nMorrigan was often noted as one of the most sexy characters of fighting games and gaming in general. In 2003, [[GameSpy]]'s Bryan Johnson ranked this \"embodiment of sexual temptation\" as the third top \"babe in games\", calling her and Capcom's answer to [[SNK]]'s [[Mai Shiranui]].<ref>Bryan \"Sir Crossforge\" Johnson, [https://web.archive.org/web/20090218114719/http://archive.gamespy.com/top10/may03/gamebabes/index3.shtml Top 10 Babes in Games], GameSpy, 4 May 2003.</ref> GameDaily placed Morrigan number nine on their 2008 list of \"hottest game babes\",<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.gamedaily.com/articles/galleries/top-25-hottest-game-babes/?page=43| title = Top 50 Hottest Game Babes on Trial| publisher = GameDaily| first = Chris| last = Buffa| date = 21 March 2008 | accessdate =29 July 2013 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080603080315/http://www.gamedaily.com/articles/galleries/top-25-hottest-game-babes/?page=43 | archivedate=3 June 2008}}</ref> while UGO ranked Morrigan fourth in their 2011 list of the \"foxiest fighting females to ever be pixelated.\"<ref>Aubrey Sitterson, [http://www.ugo.com/games/morrigan-aensland Fighting Games' Finest Female Fighters] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120429052354/http://www.ugo.com/games/morrigan-aensland |date=29 April 2012 }}, UGO.com, 14 January 2011.</ref> GameFront staff featured her twice on their 2011 list of \"greatest boobs in video game history\", at 37th (for the ''Darkstalkers'' version, called the \"reason 12-year-olds packed [[Arcade game|arcades]] into the late '90s\") and 11th (for the ''Marvel Vs. Capcom'' version, being \"50% of all [[San Diego Comic-Con International|Comic Con]] costumes\"),<ref>GameFront Staff, [http://www.gamefront.com/the-greatest-boobs-in-video-game-history-gallery/ The Greatest Boobs In Video Game History (Gallery)], GameFront, 5 May 2011.</ref> while China's [[NetEase]] put Morrigan at fifth spot on their list of top ten big-chested \"sex goddesses\" in video games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://play.163.com/11/0509/12/73K4N45A00314K8H_3.html |title=\u80f8\u5668\u8db3\u591f\u5927\uff01\u76d8\u70b9\u6e38\u620f\u4e2d\u7684\u5341\u5927\u6027\u611f\u5973\u795e_\u7f51\u6613\u6e38\u620f\u9891\u9053 |publisher=Play.163.com |date=2011-05-09 |accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref> Morrigan's breasts were also ranked as the eight-best in gaming history by Rich Shivener of [[Joystick Division]] that same year,<ref>Rich Shivener, [http://www.joystickdivision.com/2011/08/10_incredible_chests_in_video.php 10 Incredible Chests in Video Games] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160516165638/http://www.joystickdivision.com/2011/08/10_incredible_chests_in_video.php |date=16 May 2016 }}, Joystick Division, 1 August 2011.</ref> with Italian edition of [[Tom's Games]] ranking Morrigan's cleavages as the second-best neckline in video game history in 2012,<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.tomshw.it/articoli/top-10-le-migliori-scollature-dei-videogiochi-42993-p10 |title=Morrigan Aensland \u2013 Darkstalkers \u2013 Tom's Hardware |publisher=Tomshw.it |date=2013-09-09 |accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref> as well included among \"the hottest video game breasts of all time\" by ''Playboy''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playboy.com/galleries/hottest-video-game-breasts/slide-24 |title=2-Up: The Hottest Video Game Breasts of All Time \u2013 Slide 24 |publisher=Playboy |date=2015-03-23 |accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref> In 2012, Morrigan was ranked as the \"third-hottest\" character video game history by Larry Hester of ''Complex'',<ref>Larry Hester, [http://www.complex.com/video-games/2012/06/the-50-hottest-video-game-characters/ The 50 Hottest Video Game Characters], Complex.com, 27 Jun 2012.</ref> as the fifth-sexiest woman in video games by Spanish [[IGN]],<ref>{{cite web|author=Jos\u00e9 Manuel Bringas |url=http://es.ign.com/wii/61052/feature/top-25-de-tias-buenas-de-videojuegos?p=3 |title=Top 25 de t\u00edas buenas de videojuegos \u2013 Wii |publisher=Es.ign.com |date= |accessdate=2016-07-07}}</ref> and as the \"17th-hottest\" female video game character by Kristie Bertucci of Gadget Review,<ref>Kristie Bertucci, [http://www.gadgetreview.com/2012/07/20-hottest-female-video-game-characters.html 20 hottest female video game characters (list)], Gadget Review, 5 July 2012.</ref> In 2013, Scott Marley of ''[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]]'' declared Morrigan the eighth-most attractive female video game character,<ref>Scott Marley, [http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/entertainment/video-games/video-games-news/top-ten-most-attractive-female-1789728 Top Ten Most Attractive Female Video Game Characters], Daily Record, 28 March 2013.</ref> and Steve Jenkins of [[CheatCodes.com]] ranked her as the \"seventh-hottest video game girl\" of all time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cheatcodes.com/extra/2013/10/21/top-25-hottest-video-game-girls-of-all-time/20/ |title=Top 25 Hottest Video Game Girls of All Time &#124; Page 20 of 26 &#124; CheatCodes.com Extra |publisher=Cheatcodes.com |date=2013-10-21 |accessdate=2013-11-28}}</ref> She was included among the \"old school hotties that still got it\" by Travis Hubert of Cheat Code Central in 2014,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://lists.cheatcc.com/190?page=5 | title=10 Old School Hotties That Still Got It | date=7 May 2014 | author=Huber, Travis | publisher=Cheat Code Central | accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref> and ranked as the sixth-sexiest female video game character by WatchMojo.com that same year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2Gx5Bx6PE9A|title=Top 10 Sexiest Female Video Game Characters \u2013 YouTube|author=|work=YouTube|accessdate=8 September 2014}}</ref> Similarly, Vietnam's ''[[Thanh Ni\u00ean]]'' ranked her as the seventh-most sexy female video game character in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.thanhnien.com.vn/bai-viet/2015/03/08/25-nhan-va%CC%A3t-nu%CC%83-khie%CC%81n-ca%CC%81c-game-thu%CC%89-nam-ma%CC%81t-ta%CC%A3p-trung-nha%CC%81t.5703.html|title=25 nh\u00e2n v\u1eadt n\u1eef khi\u1ebfn c\u00e1c game th\u1ee7 nam \"m\u1ea5t t\u1eadp trung\" nh\u1ea5t &#124; \u0110\u00e1nh gi\u00e1 \u2013 Ph\u00f3ng s\u1ef1 &#124; Thanh Ni\u00ean Game|publisher=Game.thanhnien.com.vn|accessdate=2015-07-16|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701142835/http://game.thanhnien.com.vn/bai-viet/2015/03/08/25-nhan-va%CC%A3t-nu%CC%83-khie%CC%81n-ca%CC%81c-game-thu%CC%89-nam-ma%CC%81t-ta%CC%A3p-trung-nha%CC%81t.5703.html|archivedate=1 July 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nUGO included Morrigan on their 2008 list of 11 \"hottest babes to ever hit the video game world,\" stating that \"one thing that video game babes have over the real-life variety is that it's much easier for a girl who's made of pixels to rock an absolutely ludicrous outfit and still look hot ... she doesn't look a year of her 300, and her appearances across the Capcom fighting franchises prove that the company has an excellent eye for the female form,\"<ref name=ugot>UGO Team, [http://www.ugo.com/games/gaming-girls/?cur=morrigan-aenslan Top 11 Girls of Gaming] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090216170443/http://ugo.com/games/gaming-girls/?cur=morrigan-aenslan |date=16 February 2009 }}, UGO.com, 15 January 2008.</ref> as well as in the 2011 list of fifty \"hottest girls in games\".<ref>UGO Team, [http://www.ugo.com/games/video-game-hotties/?cur=morrigan-darkstalkers&morepics=33 Top 50 Videogame Hotties] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081205082112/http://www.ugo.com/games/video-game-hotties/?cur=morrigan-darkstalkers&morepics=33 |date=5 December 2008 }}, UGO.com, 27 October 2011.</ref> In 2009, Gelo Gonzales of Filipino ''[[FHM]]'' listed the \"undeniably seductive\" Morrigan among the nine sexiest \"bad girls of videogame land\",<ref>Gelo Gonzales, [https://www.fhm.com.ph/lifestyle/tech/the-bad-girls-of-videogame-land The bad girls of videogame land], ''FHM'', 11 September 2009.</ref> while Manolith included her on their top lists of \"sexiest video game women\" and \"hottest female video game protagonists\".<ref>Akela Talamasca, [https://web.archive.org/web/20090802143328/http://www.manolith.com/2009/07/30/top-10-sexiest-video-game-women Top 10 Sexiest Video Game Women], Manolith, 30 July 2009.</ref><ref>The Manolith Team, [https://web.archive.org/web/20091212225855/http://www.manolith.com/2009/12/09/hottest-videogame-babes 25 Hottest Female Video Game Protagonists], Manolith, 9 December 2009.</ref> Johnny Firecloud of [[CraveOnline]] featured this \"iconic succubus\" on his 2010 list of ten \"hottest video game girls of all time\", commenting that she \"is more than just an anatomic wonder \u2013 she's also one of the single most sexually stylistic ladies in gaming land.\"<ref>Johnny Firecloud, [http://www.craveonline.com/gaming/articles/132296-the-hottest-girls-in-gaming The Hottest Girls in Gaming] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130715110711/http://www.craveonline.com/gaming/articles/132296-the-hottest-girls-in-gaming |date=15 July 2013 }}, CraveOnline, 16 November 2010.</ref> Japanator.com's Bob Muir included her on the list of \"Japanese gaming's top ten hottest girls\", stating: \"In fact, Morrigan is so popular that many people know of her sultry looks who have never touched a ''Darkstalkers'' game.\"<ref>Bob Muir, [http://www.japanator.com/japanese-gaming-s-top-ten-hottest-girls-and-guys-18305.phtml Japanese Gaming's Top Ten Hottest Girls and Guys], Japanator.com, 01.23.2011.</ref>  In 2012, she was listed as one of ten sexiest video game characters by Fernando DaQuino of Tecmundo,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tecmundo.com.br/selecao/33744-as-10-personagens-mais-sexy-dos-video-games.htm |title=As 10 personagens mais sexy dos video games |publisher=Tecmundo.com.br |date=7 December 2012 |accessdate=2014-03-02 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> [[MSN]] Malaysia included this \"shameless succubus\" among the twenty \"hottest women in video game history\",<ref>[http://tech.malaysia.msn.com/photoviewer.aspx?cp-documentid=250764311 The hottest women in video game history] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130228110539/http://tech.malaysia.msn.com/photoviewer.aspx?cp-documentid=250764311 |date=28 February 2013 }}, MSN, 21 September 2012.</ref> and UGO included her among the 99 \"hottest\" fictional women of the year, calling her inclusion the best thing about ''Marvel Vs. Capcom 3''.<ref name=ugo>[http://www.ugo.com/girls/99-hottest-fictional-women-of-2012-morrigan-aensland Morrigan Aensland \u2013 The 99 Hottest Fictional Women Of 2012] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120208144623/http://www.ugo.com/girls/99-hottest-fictional-women-of-2012-morrigan-aensland |date=8 February 2012 }}, UGO.com, 1 February 2012.</ref> John Corpuz of [[Tom's Guide]] included her on his 2013's list of twenty \"hottest video game babes\" and stated that \"when it comes to [[Fighting game#History|90s fighting games]], ''Darkstalkers''\u2019 Morrigan is the definitive poster girl.\"<ref>John Corpuz, [http://www.tomsguide.com/us/pictures-story/484-12-Video-Game-Girls-Babes-Hottest-Characters-Stunning.html 20 of The Hottest Video Game Babes] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130522193347/http://www.tomsguide.com/us/pictures-story/484-12-Video-Game-Girls-Babes-Hottest-Characters-Stunning.html |date=22 May 2013 }}, Tom's Guide, 26 April 2013.</ref> A poll for the most erotic girl in the history of fighting games conducted by Japanese web portal Goo had had Morrigan take the fourth place out of 50 contesters in 2016;<ref>http://news.nicovideo.jp/watch/nw2426054</ref> she was later voted the third in a 2018 poll.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ranking.goo.ne.jp/column/4951/|script-title=ja:[\u30b3\u30e9\u30e0] \u683c\u30b2\u30fc\u53f2\u4e0a\u6700\u3082\u30bb\u30af\u30b7\u30fc\u306a\u5973\u5b50\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u306f\uff1f 2\u4f4d\u300c\u4e0d\u77e5\u706b\u821e\u300d|website=goo\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0|language=ja|access-date=2018-07-30}}</ref>\n\n===Other reception===\nIn 2008, Morrigan was included on a list of top \"chicks behaving badly\" by IGN's Scott Cullura for her \"penchant for magic and kick-ass fighting moves,\" her outfit described as \"one that would make even [[Jenna Jameson]] blush.\"<ref>Scott Cullura, [http://stars.ign.com/articles/863/863436p8.html Top 50 Chicks Behaving Badly: Round 1], IGN, 31 March 2008.</ref> While Zoomin Games named her costume as the second-most sexy outfit in games,<ref>[http://www.zoomin.tv/site/gamesvideo.cfm/lang/es-es/video/7paN-dqMr4g Top 5 \u2013 Sexiest game outfits] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130418212903/http://www.zoomin.tv/site/gamesvideo.cfm/lang/es-es/video/7paN-dqMr4g |date=18 April 2013 }}, Zoomin.TV, 19 October 2012.</ref> Charlie Barratt of GamesRadar cited Morrigan as one example of what they considered \"the most shameless\u2014and least surprising\u2014character clich\u00e9 of all time\" which is \"the half-naked woman.\"<ref name=\"gamesradar7\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/the-top-7-lazy-character-cliches/?page=7|title=The Top 7...Lazy Character Clich\u00e9s|first=Charlie|last=Barratt|publisher=GamesRadar|date=21 July 2008|accessdate=16 June 2014}}</ref> Morrigan was featured in a list of ten \"babes who shouldn't meet your mom\" by [[GameDaily]] in 2008,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.gamedaily.com/articles/galleries/ten-babes-who-should-and-10-babes-who-shouldnt-meet-your-mom/?page=6 | title= Don't take her to mom: Morrigan (Darkstalkers series)|publisher=GameDaily | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080716054223/http://www.gamedaily.com/articles/galleries/ten-babes-who-should-and-10-babes-who-shouldnt-meet-your-mom/?page=6 | archivedate=16 July 2008}}</ref> as well as in a list of ten \"game girls you wouldn't dare to date\" by [[Virgin Media]] in 2010.<ref>[http://www.virginmedia.com/games/inpictures/bad-date.php?ssid=2 Morrigan Aensland (Darkstalkers) \u2013 Bad Date], Virgin Media.</ref> In 2011, Rich Knight of ''Complex'' pitted her against [[Rayne (Bloodrayne)|Agent Rayne]] in the \"battle of the beauties\" feature, comparing them to \"the sexy [[Goth subculture|goth]] girls you were too afraid to ask out in high school\" and choosing Morrigan,<ref>Rich Knight, [http://www.complex.com/video-games/2011/11/battle-of-the-beauties-gamings-hottest-female-characters-face-off#11 Battle of the Beauties: Gaming's Hottest Female Characters Face Off], Complex.com, 9 November 2011.</ref> but Richard Coombs of [[Blistered Thumbs]] ranked her as number one video game woman \"you wouldn\u2019t want to be with\" as \"that would probably be the scariest romance you could ever be in.\"<ref>Richard Coombs, [https://web.archive.org/web/20110418073320/http://www.blisteredthumbs.net/2011/04/the-top-9-women/ The Top 9 Video Game Women You Wouldn\u2019t Want to be With], Blistering Thumbs, 15 April 2011.</ref> ''Complex'' featured \"Morrigan's bloodlust\" on their list of \"14 aspects of our perfect Valentine\u2014one video game girl at a time\" to build a perfect woman on [[Valentine's Day]] 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2012/02/weird-science-building-the-perfect-valentine-from-our-14-favorite-video-game-girls/1|title=Weird Science: Building The Perfect Valentine From Our 14 Favorite Video Game Girls \u2013 Complex|date=14 February 2012|work=Complex}}</ref> [[Game Revolution]] included an alleged rumor of Morrigan's romance with Nintendo's [[Princess Daisy]] in their 2014 [[April Fools' Day]] feature.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/features/the-gamerevolution-rumor-roundup#/slide/6 |title=The GameRevolution Rumor Round-Up |publisher=Gamerevolution.com |date= 1 April 2014 |accessdate=2014-04-12 |author=Ryan Bates}}</ref>\n\nDespite her popularity, Morrigan, along with the ''Darkstalkers'' cast in general, has not been as well-received for her presence in the [[Darkstalkers (TV series)|1995 cartoon series]]. Rachel Jagielski of [[VentureBeat]] described her as the otherwise \"normally sensual succubus\" who \"looked, if not terrible, really boring\" in the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2011/04/04/discovering-the-darkstalkers-cartoon/|title=Discovering the Darkstalkers Cartoon |publisher=VentureBeat|first=Rachel|last=Jagielski|date=4 April 2011|accessdate=17 June 2014}}</ref> Ryan Winterhalter of GamesRadar called the character \"old and creepy,\"<ref name=\"gamesradar\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/five-truly-horrendous-tv-shows-based-upon-videogames/?page=2|title=Five truly horrendous TV shows based on videogames|first=Ryan|last=Winterhalter|publisher=GamesRadar|date=8 July 2010|accessdate=8 June 2014}}</ref> and Hardcore Gaming 101 opined she \"look[ed] frightening in most close-ups.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/darkstalkers/darkstalkers3.htm|title=Hardcore Gaming 101: Darkstalkers/Vampire|publisher=Hardcoregaming101.net|accessdate=18 June 2014}}</ref> 411mania.com called this version of Morrigan \"awful\" and her [[Scottish English|Scottish accent]] therein \"inappropriately wrong\", castigating the show itself as \"the worst video game cartoon in history\".<ref name=\"411mania\">{{cite web|url=http://www.411mania.com/games/news/90204/The-Hall-of-Shame-11.12.08:-Top-5-Most-Shameful-Video-Game-Cartoons.htm#3tykvLSUPtUJm2pP.99|title=Hall of Shame: Top 5 Most Shameful Video Game Cartoons|first=Vincent|last=Chiucchi|publisher=411Mania.com|date=12 November 2008|accessdate=8 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714120151/http://www.411mania.com/games/news/90204/The-Hall-of-Shame-11.12.08:-Top-5-Most-Shameful-Video-Game-Cartoons.htm#3tykvLSUPtUJm2pP.99|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Night Warriors: Darkstalkers' Revenge (anime)|The anime version]] has been received much better; for instance, Bryn Williams of ''Gamers' Republic'' chose the \"extremely erotic\" scene of Morrigan taking a bath as the \"highlight moment\" in his review of the third episode.<ref>''Gamers' Republic'' issue 8 (July 1999), page 107.</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Video games}}\n*[[List of Darkstalkers characters|List of ''Darkstalkers'' characters]]\n*[[List of succubi in fiction]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=\"note\"}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* Official websites: [http://www.capcom.co.jp/VR/chara_morrigan.html ''Vampire Resurrection''], [http://www.capcom.co.jp/VR/chara_morrigan.html ''Marvel vs. Capcom Infinite''] {{in lang|ja}}\n* Morrigan's [https://web.archive.org/web/20140302090546/http://strategywiki.org/wiki/Darkstalkers/Characters/Morrigan ''Darkstalkers''] and [http://strategywiki.org/wiki/Marvel_vs._Capcom/Characters/Morrigan ''Marvel vs. Capcom 2''] entries at StrategyWiki.org\n\n{{Darkstalkers series}}\n\n[[Category:Adoptee characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Capcom protagonists]]\n[[Category:Darkstalkers characters]]\n[[Category:Deity characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Demon characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Female characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional bisexual females]]\n[[Category:Fictional British people in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters who can duplicate themselves]]\n[[Category:Fictional half-demons]]\n[[Category:Fictional Scottish people]]\n[[Category:Fictional succubi]]\n[[Category:LGBT characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Marvel vs. Capcom fighters]]\n[[Category:Shapeshifter characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Twin characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Queen characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Video game characters in anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Video game characters in comics]]\n[[Category:Video game characters in film]]\n[[Category:Video game characters in television]]\n[[Category:Video game characters introduced in 1994]]\n[[Category:Video game characters who can teleport]]\n[[Category:Video game characters who use magic]]\n[[Category:Video game characters with slowed aging]]\n[[Category:Video game mascots]]\n[[Category:Video game secret characters]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox video game character\n|name=Morrigan Aensland\n|image=Morrigan(Darkstalkers).png\n|caption=Morrigan in ''[[Darkstalkers Resurrection]]'' (2013)\n|series=[[Darkstalkers]]\n|firstgame=''[[Darkstalkers: The Night Warriors]]'' (1994)\n|voice = {{Collapsible list|title=[[English language|English]]\n|[[Saffron Henderson]] <small>(American animated series)</small>\n|[[Kathleen Barr]] 